    "summary": "I have applied permaculture principles to create comprehensive plans for sustainable agriculture, water management, energy systems, social considerations and ensured the realization of self-sustaining systems in harmony with nature. Prior to this, I worked as a Communications & Digital Educator at Eco?L\u00f3gico, where I produced video and text reports on social and environmental topics, disseminated project information, and provided media training to organizations and NGOs. Also possess extensive experience as a corporate communications video maker, video photography director, photojournalist and e-learning video consultant, working with various renowned brands and organizations.\nMy educational background includes courses on resilience to climate change risks and natural disasters at the University for Peace, advanced permaculture design at Unipermacultura, and urban socio-environmental practices. With a diverse skill set encompassing circular economy, urban design, community outreach, and permaculture. I\u2019m also well-equipped to contribute to sustainable initiatives,Communication/Media Production and environmental projects.\n\nSkills:\n- Permaculture Design\n- Circular Economy\n- Urban Design\n- Sustainability Analysis\n- Communication and Media Production\n- Environmental Awareness\n- Project Management\n- Stakeholder Collaboration\n- Video Production and Editing\n- Social Media Marketing\n\nCareer highlights:\n- Conceptualized and implemented sustainable systems as a Permaculture Designer, leading to the successful realization of self-sustaining environments in line with nature (BaseCamp Eco-resorts).\n- Produced engaging video content and media training for organizations and NGOs, contributing to effective communication and awareness of social and environmental issues (Eco?L\u00f3gico).\n- Created corporate communications videos for renowned companies, effectively conveying brand messages and contributing to their marketing success (DFilms).",
